## Environment Variable Reference

| Variable | Dev | Prod |
|---|---|---|
| ENVIRONMENT | development | production |
| OPENAI_API_KEY | your key | your key |
| OPENAI_MODEL | gpt-4o-mini | gpt-4o-mini |
| PINECONE_API_KEY | your key | your key |
| PINECONE_INDEX_NAME | home-intelligence | home-intelligence |
| LANGCHAIN_API_KEY | your key | your key |
| LANGCHAIN_PROJECT | home-intelligence-agent-dev | home-intelligence-agent-prod |
| LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2 | true | true |

---

## What You'll Be Able to Say on Day One

*"I built a production LangGraph ReAct agent for home intelligence. The agent
reasons autonomously and decides which tools to call вҖ” it can search my home
documents via RAG in Pinecone, search the web for contractors and pricing, and
analyze photos of things around the house. It maintains conversation memory
within a session so I can ask follow-up questions naturally. The agent also
outputs structured actions like calendar events and tasks, which get queued
and executed by an n8n automation layer running on a Raspberry Pi that polls
the API. The whole thing has a Streamlit frontend, FastAPI backend, structured
logging, LangSmith tracing, evals gating production deploys, and CI/CD
through GitHub Actions."*

---

## Part 2 (Future вҖ” Pinned Ideas)

- Persistent conversation memory via PostgresSaver (survives server restarts)
- RAG validation (are the retrieved docs actually relevant before using them?)
- Answer groundedness check (is the answer supported by the docs?)
- Multi-agent coordination (separate agents for documents, costs, scheduling)
- Proactive n8n workflows (seasonal maintenance reminders, warranty expiration alerts)
- Additional tools (appliance recall lookup, permit requirement search, cost calculator)
- Conversation history endpoint (GET /api/threads/{thread_id}/history)